channel.title: TO MOD TAHAROK(Your box is full)
channel.description: Okay, last night I had one of my friends help me get a server. We were almost done and I went to click the "runserver" thing and a screen popped up then went away before you could read anything. Then we clicked the compile button and typed in c to compile it. Then this message popped up saying something like "You do no have JDK 5.0 or JDK 6.0." So I downloaded it and tried again. Same message. Than my friend sent me his JDK over msn and we tried again. Same message. Then again today, my other friend sent me his and we tried again. Same message so I tried downloading it again and got the same message. Then I followed your tutorials instructions and tried it again and I got the same message. I have added you on MSN and I am waiting for you to get on and help me. I have no clue what is going wrong. Also, I am now following your instructions for making a server. And I cannot find my router. I typed in my IP adress that I got from the No-Ip website thing and google popped up.... Can you log on MSN and help me figure this dumb thing out. I am having a ton of trouble. Also, add me on msn just incase I typed your email in wrong, my email is "kohrs87@mchsi.com"[br][size=1]Posted on: April 07, 2007, 08:08:18 PM[/size][hr]Anyone else that wants to help can also. ;)[br][size=1]Posted on: April 07, 2007, 08:08:57 PM[/size][hr]Anyone at all?[br][size=1]Posted on: April 07, 2007, 08:10:39 PM[/size][hr]Bump. Lol.

you got probally jdk 6 update 1

put this in compiler …

this in runserver
